 Forget the notion that it is meant to unite the country. How that could be possible when ODM has put a knife in the middle of Jubilee Party and twisted it to divide its key alma maters President Kenyatta and VP Ruto? The division in the party has created a domino effect in the country and the citizens are split down the middle too as a result of the departure from handshake ‘unity’ and fall out from the BBI.
Focus on statesmanship
There is no one whose credibility hangs in the balance as a result of the fall out on BBI than former Prime Minister Raila Odinga. He risks turning into the emperor with no clothes as his party totters around him instead of advising him that perhaps the time is right for him to scale back on political ambitions and focus more on statesmanship, lest his star wanes further.
This is not the first time Mr Odinga has tried to siphon a position within the government through backroom deals. He somehow remains relevant within the governments formed since 2002 as he has become clever at finding a wriggle room to retain power. Understandably, every election he has been involved in has ended in a farce with claims of rigging and violence but somehow, he has always come out unscathed unlike his supporters as he shelters in whichever government is in place.



