This time around, I believe his push for BBI to pave way for another post for him in government come 2022 is bound to paint him in terrible light. If I were his disciple, I would advise him to leave while still on top.
His silence on unsavoury means being employed, such as use of public officials and State resources to gather signatures for the BBI referendum and his insensitivity towards the impact of Covid-19 on the population and slowing down economy only shows how far he is prepared to go to regain power.
Mr Odinga does not need to stoop so low to rely on BBI to keep him relevant in the political scene. He has nothing more to prove. He must walk away now with head held high while we still remember him as one of the key architects of democracy in Kenya if not Africa.



