Tension and uncertainties
We take cognisance of the fact that he will never get back the many years he lost in jail as he fought for democracy. We salute him for his resilience. However, neither would he be able to recover his credibility both locally and internationally should he carry own tearing apart a country he helped to free from impunity.
The U-turn by Mr Odinga witnessed after the disputed 2017 presidential election left many aghast. The handshake came on the back of tension and uncertainties in the country.
The initial reason given for the handshake was to unite the country but that is now lost in acerbic wrestle for power for 2022 with Mr Odinga bang in the middle of it – again! The truth behind the handshake and BBI is getting economical by the day and with it chipping little layers of credibility from the former Prime Minister day by day.
As Kenny Rogers sang, Raila needs to know when to walk away and when to run. The time is now for him to look back at the success he made of bringing democracy to the country and bask in that glory rather than muddy the waters for himself in his winter years. He risks ending up in the lions’ lair like biblical David rather than the Canaan of his dreams.



